Azure Power Global Limited Key Developments

Azure Power Global Limited Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Revenue Guidance for Fiscal Year 2018 Ending March 31, 2018
Jun 19 17
Azure Power Global Limited reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported operating revenues of INR 1,317,577,000 compared to INR 767,237,000 a year ago. Operating income was INR 660,391,000 compared to INR 320,450,000 a year ago. Profit before income tax was INR 338,459,000 compared to loss before income tax of INR 355,122,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company was INR 313,605,000 or INR 13 per basic and diluted share compared to INR 597,422,000 or INR 501 per basic and diluted share a year ago. This was primarily due to increase in revenue, lower interest expense and a foreign exchange gain realised during the quarter ended March 31, 2017. Net cash used in operating activities was INR 250,939,000 compared to INR 795,196,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was INR 974,390,000 compared to INR 512,584,000 a year ago. The increase in revenue was driven by the commissioning of new projects.

For the year, the company reported operating revenues of INR 4,182,985,000 compared to INR 2,626,148,000 a year ago. Operating income was INR 1,963,472,000 compared to INR 1,074,878,000 a year ago. Loss before income tax was INR 299,236,000 compared to INR 1,327,095,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company was INR 1,172,645,000 or INR 111 per basic and diluted share compared to INR 1,650,189,000 or INR 1,722 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was INR 27,190,000 compared to net cash provided by operating activities of INR 733,868,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was INR 3,010,037,000 compared to INR 1,762,659,000 a year ago.


The company is giving revenue guidance for fiscal year 2018 ending March 31, 2018 of USD 118 - 125 million. In addition, the company expects that 1,000 - 1,200 MWs will be operational by March 31, 2018.


