Azure Power - A Leading Solar Power Company in India















































 


 
Menu
Home
Utilities
Commercial
About Us
Investor
Careers
 






PAN India portfolio of solar assets in 18 states

Azure Power Solar Plant, Jodhpur, Rajasthan | 100 MW




India's first utility scale solar project

Azure Power Solar Plant, Awan, Punjab | 2 MW




India's first distributed MW scale rooftop solar project

Azure Power Solar Plant, Gandhinagar, Gujarat | 2.5 MW










We sell Solar Power on long term fixed price contracts
at prices which in many cases are at or below prevailing alternatives









We have successfully brought down the cost of power from INR 17.91 /kWh in 2009 to INR 4.67 /kWh in 2016




Low Cost of  Energy
We have lowered our cost of energy through value engineering, operational performance monitoring and efficient financial strategy. This allows us to deliver cost-effective energy for our customers. Our in-house EPC expertise lowers system costs and our advanced in-house operations and maintenance capability allows us to increase power yields and monitor project performance near real-time. Coupled with our efficient financial strategy, we believe that we are able to offer low-cost solar power solutions at high efficiency yields.




Strong Value Proposition for Our Customers
We manage the entire development and operation process, providing customers with long  term fixed price PPAs, as a result of solar not being subject to variable commodity prices Our in-house focus on high engineering standards and asset quality ensures high levels  of availability and service to our customers. 





We have lowered our cost of energy through value engineering, operational performance monitoring and efficient financial strategy









Our integrated project development, EPC, financing and O&M services has allowed us to generate efficiencies of scale that further drive down system costs 




Integrated Profile
As opposed to relying on third-party providers, our integrated profile affords us greater control over project development, construction and operation, which provides us with greater insight and certainty on our construction costs and timeline. Coupled with our low cost profile, our greater insight supports competitive new project bids at prevailing market prices, not at our direct costs.




Strong Community Partnership
We hire from local communities and generally lease land with few alternative uses, providing local communities with a stream of discretionary cash flow without displacing alternative businesses. As a result we are able to build long-term community relationships, which allows us to improve our time of completion, further reducing project development risk. 





"Not only did the plant provide electricity to all the nearby underserved villages, it also provided employement to most of us in the village"
- Jagir Singh, Lessor - Project land, Punjab








